	   <tr><td colspan=2>WoW! Phat Lewtz! That R0xx0rs Dewd!<br><br>...<br><br>In all seriousness, farming cat pelts is a sketchy occupation at best. The HQ pelts are used for tailoring quivers, which is often used to get tailoring up to 115. However, it depends a lot on finding the right person at the right time. If ya try to sell HQ cat pelts in the bazaar for 20pp a throw, you're gonna be there for a Looooooooooong time. That being said, there's a lot of money to be made marketing the RIGHT kind of tailoring supplies.<br><br>One of the best methods is Heady Kiolas, easily the most ANNOYING GOD DAMN COMBINE IN THE GAME. However, they're easy to make and you can probably sell them for about 3 to 5 plat each to poor bastards like me who decided to take up tailoring. They cost well under a plat each to make, so the return is pretty solid. It's not a hard combine to do, but tailors (like me) gradually grow to hate it beyond all reason for the simple fact that you need 4 of them to do a single combine for wu tailoring. I wouldn't be the least bit suprised if I've gone through 100 stacks of the bloody things.<br><br>And then of course there's the old standby... Spider silk. Long as you're in EK kill crag spiders. Should be pretty decent exp too depending on your level. The crags drop up to 8 silk each, and the other giant spider thinggies drop up to 4, your milage may vary.<br><br>Silk itself fetches a pretty good price up at the bazaar, or you can combine it in to swatches. silk should sell from 3 to 5 pp each, with swatches being like 5 to 10 each, which rounds out to 100 to 200pp a stack.<br><br>These are just a couple examples. You have hit on something gwito, the fact that high level characters starting on tradeskills do NOT want to be bothered with farming greenies for parts. Now, I don't know if others could consistantly get 20pp per HQ cat pelt, but there are other options that you and others could try to make money. Just look at dropped items that people doing tradeskills are likely to need in bulk and start marketing them.<br><br>It's probably one of the safest ways for a lower level character to make cash.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar, arch nemesis of the evil squirrel empire, leader of the Defiant Heroes, currently battling the evil flu deamons.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
