	   <tr><td colspan=2>Never knock a fire pet. Yes it has the least HPs, but the fire pet tears through most MoBs so fast that you can't tell the difference. It is by far more mana efficient to use fire over any other pet (pre 49). The fire pet's DS is pet's lvl + 1 I believe. Correct me if I'm wrong. I soloed fire pet all the way to 48, when I soloed. This changes at lvl 49. At 49, your earth pet becomes way more beneficial than any other pet you have in solo situations. Simply put, they can survive the beating that's being dished to them. At 50 MS2 isn't bad, they do the most dmg because 90% of the time they don't waste time casting, but 49 earth is still tougher. At 51, your new earth pet rocks, has about 2700 HPs, occasionally quads for 58 a shot (your own persnal warrior). This is the one you'll probably be usng for the next few lvls. Now at 55, whether I solo or group determines which pet I use. 53 Air if fighting casters, but 54 water pet in most cases. In groups, just get behind MoB and let pet go, or learn how to pet kite for soloing. (54 water is your own personal rogue - 168BS). 54's water advantage is also his quick regen, if not pet kiting, making for little downtime. I have a 58 Mage friend, with a killer 57 earth pet, so I suspect I'll be going back to earth once I hit 57.<br>Point being, all pets have their uses, choice of pet is a preference, but some pets are better in different situations and lvls. Test them all, you'll find the one to use with practice.<br>&nbsp;<br>Sticks and stones may break my bones,<br>But not if you can't touch me. 8)</td></tr>
