	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103559473218135><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103559473218135>RE: Level 31 huniting grounds</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103559473218135#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93315><span id=Scholar>Jeroo</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>45 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 25th 9:31 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.02]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, soloing will easily beat grouping experience at these levels.<br><br>Best xp for 30-40?<br><br>24-32 Needlites in Echo Caverns<br>30-34 Dwarves on Sister Isle in OOT<br>34-39 Cynthia in Rathe Mountains<br>29-36 Rangers/Druids in EC<br><br>That should get you started.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the needlites, use your fire pet.  Needlites hit really, really fast for 2-20 pts of damage each hit.  They bash themselves to death against your fire pet.  You'll also max out your defense here, which is important down the road.<br><br>For the dwarves, there's two on the northwest side of Sister Isle, and a 3rd over by the dwarven merchant on the west side.  Killing them will ruin your KaladimCitizen faction, which is not a big deal.  Use your 29 fire pet, pull with your most current debuff, and wait until the dwarf is down to 75% before nuking.  You can easily split the two on the northwest corner of the isle, and the 3rd will not agro the merchant when you pull them.  They drop 0-5pp and various words, runes, etc.  6 minute spawn, so space them out and you'll be hopping to keep up with them.<br><br>Cynthia is in the gypsy camp closest to the Lake Rathetear zone in Rathe Mts.  She's a wizard, so if you have resist gear, that would help.  Fire pet works nicely here, as well.  You can attack her in the middle of the camp without anyone else agroing.  Send in the pet, debuff, and nuke hard and fast.  You'll use 2 of your best nukes to drop her.  Another 6 minute spawn, but her xp is outstanding.  She drops 0-5pp, plus gems, words, runes, etc.  You can sell right in the middle of the camp.  NO FACTION HIT!<br><br>The Rangers in EC are an incredible camp as long as you can split it.  Ask a druid nearby (the place is littered with them) to Harmony one and you take the other.  Use your fire pet, and nuke hard.  The spawn is 5 minutes, so space them out a bit.  They drop FS, 0-5pp, words, etc.  You can sell right at the druid merchant.<br><br>This will destroy your druid faction beyond repair, so if the idea of porting with invis on bothers you, don't do it.  But the money you will make is incredible for the level -- I usually averaged well over 1000-1200pp per level.<br>&nbsp;<br>--<br>Jeroo Ashstaff</td></tr>
