	   <tr><td colspan=2>Summoned foci are well worth it. That being said, the only ones I really use are the ring, the braclet and the earring. <br><br>For mages the component removal necklace isn't THAT important until you start using pearls as regents, tho occasionally I will pop a necklace on just to see if I can't reduce my cat's eye consumption from the phantom armor line. Not that they cost much, but it gets annoying having to go buy them, particularly when you have to use 4 cat's eyes for one cast.<br><br>The buff shawl I rarely use. Mainly because I can't for the life of me figure out what the heck it does. As far as I can tell it either increases duration of buffs you cast, or increases duration of buffs cast on you. One of these days I'll figure out which. That being said, about the only time I would use it is if I'm gettin KEI or buffing for a raid.<br><br>The braclet you should always have. It increases damage from both spells and procs, and frankly I'm amazed we're not getting asked for more of these. Not just from wizzies, but from tanks.<br><br>The earring comes in very handy during almost any situation. When you're solo it means you don't have to worry as much about taking aggro from your pet, and in a group or a raid it means you can nuke harder and faster without having to worry about getting ripped in two by whatever you're nuking. About the only time I don't use one is if I'm pet kiting, in which case you want all the aggro you can get.<br><br>The ring is pretty handy. Not necessiary, but handy. Particularly when you're getting beat down by a couple of things and the reduced casting time on gate MIGHT just save your life.<br><br>Now, talking of the reccomended levels. I know if you're below the reccomended level you don't get all the stat bonuses, but I THINK that the effect still works the same way. If you're above the reccomended level you get all the stat bonuses and the effect should still work the same way.<br><br>So basically when you get the spell, use it until you get the upgrade. Hopefully that answers your question winter.<br><br>To continue, I'm not entirely sure what the difference is between the three levels of the foci, but there are a few possibilities. Either the percentage goes up depending on the level (ie: 10 percent damage increase to 15, to 20 on the braclet) or it will only effect certain levels of spell casts.<br><br>Frankly, foci has been a bit of a grey area for most of eq since their release. Much of the information is either apocryphal or totally inaccurate. In the interests of NOT contributing to this innacuracy, if anyone knows of anything I've gotten wrong or failed to mention in this post please speak up. Hopefully we can all learn something.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar<br>53rd season, Leader of the Defiant Heroes[tm], arch nemesis of the evil squirrel empire.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
