	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've made an observation about the rings.&nbsp;&nbsp;The information I've found all says that spells with a longer cast time than 9.5 seconds are not affected.  The level 44 shield spell has a 12 second cast time without the ring, and 10 point something second with the ring.  The ring does activate when I'm casting my shield spell.  Also, if you right click your spell gem, it will tell you the exact time reduction, i.e. &quot;cast time 10 seconds. Your cast time 8.5 seconds&quot;.  Perhaps we still haven't gotten accurate information on these summoned focus items.<br><br>The summoned focus items I generally wear are the ring, earring, bracelet and mantle.  It does still frost me a bit that I have to give up so many int. points for these items, but the payoff does seem to be there.<br><br>Keep in mind, even when you're higher level than the focus item recommends, you're not necessarily casting SPELLS of a higher level.  We spend a few minutes and a bit of mana summoning to get set up for hunting.  These are (usually) from lower level spells. Decrease casting time?  Save mana?  Oh yeah.<br><br>It is odd to me that more people (especially those casting all the buffs) don't seem to realize how beneficial these items are.  I always offer them to groupmates. The bracer is usually the only thing people want.  Perhaps we're not advertizing their benefits enough.<br>&nbsp;<br>Yanari, Witch of Felwithe</td></tr>
